          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Architecture Overview"
            }
          ],
          "type": "h2"
        }
      ]
    },
    "guide-heading": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "Building a Frontend for Headless Plone",
      "value": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Building a Frontend for Headless Plone"
            }
          ],
          "type": "h2"
        }
      ]
    },
    "guide-text": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "A 12-step guide to building a frontend for Headless Plone, applicable to any framework.",
      "value": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "The steps involved in creating a frontend are roughly the same for all frameworks:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "p"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Create a route for any path which goes to a single page (e.g., in Nuxt.js create pages/[..slug].vue)"
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The page has a template with static parts of your theme like header and footer. Check content type to render each differently."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "On page setup, take the path and make a REST API call to the contents endpoint to get the JSON for this page."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Fill title etc from the content metadata."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "For navigation, use @expand to return navigation data in the same call. Create a nav component using this JSON."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "For Blocks: create a Block component that takes id and block JSON, check @type to determine rendering, call recursively for containers, iterate blocks_layout to render."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Create helpers: URL generation for links (convert API-relative URLs to frontend URLs), image URL generation (blocks have image data in many formats)."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Listing Blocks: Use the Listing Helpers (staticBlocks/expandListingBlocks) or make your own REST API query calls."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Redirects: Handle REST API redirects as internal redirects in your framework. For SSG, query all redirects at generate time."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Error Pages: Handle REST API errors with appropriate status codes."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Search Blocks: Render facets/filters, build queries using the REST API querystring endpoint."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "Form Blocks: Render field types, produce compatible JSON submissions to the form-block endpoint, handle validation and thank you page."
                }
              ],
              "type": "li"
            }
          ],
          "type": "ol"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "See the example frontends for reference implementations: Nuxt.js, Next.js, and F7-Vue."
            }
          ],
          "type": "p"
        }
      ]
    },
    "diagram-text": {
      "@type": "slate",
      "plaintext": "You could think of it as splitting Volto into two parts, Rendering and CMS UI/Admin UI while keeping the same UI and then making the Rendering part easily replaceable with other implementations.",
      "value": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "You could think of it as splitting Volto into two parts, Rendering and CMS UI/Admin UI while keeping the same UI and then making the Rendering part easily replaceable with other implementations."
            }
          ],
          "type": "p"
        }
      ]
    },
